OL,7,FPatients on her ward ranged from
OL,8,Fpeople with schizophrenia, depression
OL,9,Fand addiction issues. She said fights
OL,10,Fwould occasionally break out, which
OL,11,Fmade her feel unsafe.
OL,13,FShe began to think: "This is not the
OL,14,Fenvironment I want to be in, this is
OL,15,Fnot an environment I feel safe in."
OL,17,FRemaining in a psychiatric unit for
OL,18,Fthree months, Georgia's condition
OL,19,Fbecame so severe she was eventually
OL,20,Fsent to a specialist eating disorder
OL,21,Funit in England.
